[normal]The legal department, currently comprised of four full-time lawye
[normal]rs, three field workers and an expert consultant, has grown to become among the most important tools in RHR’s struggle against land takeovers in the Occupied Territories. The last few years have seen 
[normal]successes
[normal] in precedent setting cases in which we have ma
[normal]naged
[normal] 
[normal]to 
[normal]return lands to Palestinian owners
[normal]. We are still 
[normal]adjudicating several potentially precedent-setting cases dealing with settler land takeovers and discriminatory planning leading to 
[normal]the ongoing threat of 
[normal]home demolitions.  
[normal]Despite these successes, 
[normal]RHR is 
[normal]still
[normal] deal
[normal]ing
[normal] with
[normal] the 
[normal]daily 
[normal]struggle
[normal] of the Occupation - creeping annexation, displacement, settler violence, and State-backed restrictions withholding basic living conditions from many Palestinians. RHR's lawyers work to thwart displacement of Pal
[normal]estinians by preventing encroachment and expropriation of privately owned Palestinian lands, protecting farmers’ rights to access their lands, supporting the field work of our partner organizations and our own field department, and demanding better enforce
[normal]ment of existing laws that do protect Palestinians’ rights.
[normal] 
[normal]Most of legal work is concentrated in the South Hebron Hills, but we do 
[normal]work 
[normal]on specific cases 
[normal]throughout the Occupied Territories
[normal]. 
[normal]It is RHR’s goal to
[normal] continue to
[normal] expand our work
[normal] geographically
[normal] and apply our successes to all of the Occupied Palestinian Territories. 
[normal]Expansion of legal cases will continue into the Hebron district and Bethlehem regions, where, in the last two years, we have taken on several cases of land encroachment and takeovers
[normal] 
[normal]with much 
[normal]success
[normal]. 
[normal]RHR is currently the only organization working in the Bethlehem / Hebron district in representing land owners. 
