[normal]8)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Monitoring progress and evidence in each case is critical to our work in the Israeli courts and in submitting complaints and appeals to the Civil Administration, the army and the police. 
[normal]To this end, t
[normal]he legal department puts great emphasis on tabulation o
[normal]f cases of human rights violations, actions taken in each case, and follow up actions required.  Detailed tables are kept by RHR lawyers of the successes (or progress) and impact of each and every case.  Two critical components are used to support this wor
[normal]k and assist in monitoring the progress with each case:
[normal]9)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Our best tool for the evaluation of the legal work is the success 
[normal]in guaranteeing farmers access to their lands, 
[normal]returning lands to their owners and the halting of land encroachment. 
[normal]The number of 
[normal]new 
[normal]and ongoing 
[normal]cases 
[normal]measures our effectiveness and success. More and more land owners approach us based on these success
[normal]es
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]Over the last decade, RHR has succeeded in cha
[normal]nging the status quo
[normal]. We have 
[normal]guaranteed Palestinian farmers safe access to their agricultural lands and water sources by 
[normal]building and maintaining grassroots contacts with local Palestinian villagers, 
[normal]refining our coordination efforts with the Israeli Defe
[normal]nse forces and relying on the contingent of Israeli and international volunteers who accompany farmers to their lands throughout the year. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]10)
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]Our 
[normal]landmark High Court victory in 2006
[normal] 
[normal]stated that 
[normal]the Israeli security forces are obliged to ensure that farmers are able to access their lands without harassment and intimidation. 
[normal]In reality, Palestinian landowners in Area C are still intimidated, harassed and prevented from accessing their lands. Radica
[normal]l settlers use violence and provocation to prevent farmers from being able to reach their lands. 
[normal]It is 
[normal]RHR’s presence in the field 
[normal]which 
[normal]ensures that the security forces are indeed fulfilling their responsibilities to protect farmers.  
[normal]R
[normal]adical settlers are
[normal] often discouraged from attacking small groups of farmers and their families
[normal] when we are there to protect them
[normal]. Documenting incidents of harassment and violence and using the media to publicize these events
[normal] puts increasing pressure on the security forces t
[normal]o carry out their court mandated job. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]11)
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]It is essential that RHR continues its work of guaranteeing Palestinian farmers access to their property
[normal]. 
[normal]Letting lands lie fallow leads to their takeover
[normal] either by settlers from settlements adjacent to these lands o
[normal]r by the State
[normal]. Ottoman law, still 
[normal]applicable
[normal] in Area C, states that uninterrupted cultivation of land for a period of ten years, without objections from any party, grants the farmer rights to the land. In absence of such rights, the land reverts to the 
[normal]S
[normal]t
[normal]ate. 
[normal]It is critical, therefore, that l
[normal]andowners continue 
[normal]to 
[normal]work their lands not only to allow them to continue to subsist from their produce, but to ensure its ongoing ownership. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]12)
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]In addition to the importance of our presence in the field, RHR plant
[normal]s
[normal] 
[normal]about 
[normal]3
[normal],000 
[normal]saplings 
[normal]during the planting season in the fall/winter on lands in danger of being taken over or where trees have been destroyed 
[normal]in “price tag” attacks 
[normal]or on lands our legal team is fighting to return to its owners. These endangered lands are a
[normal]lmost always located near politically radical settlements or illegal outposts or fall between the Green Line and the Separation Barrier throughout areas of the West Bank. Our legal staff and field staff work hand in hand in enabling 
[normal]these planting activiti
[normal]es to go ahead. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]13)
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]The highlight of our annual activities is the Olive Tree Campaign which takes place 
[normal]in the fall each year. RHR OT and field staff and tens of volunteers accompany farmers to their lands to assist in picking olives. 
[normal]During the Olive Tree C
[normal]ampaign, w
[normal]e coordinate with security forces throughout the West Bank in order to allow the farmers to access their lands. We have seen increased willingness of security forces to coordinate olive harvest days with us
[normal], but w
[normal]e need to be vigilant in ensuring
[normal] that sufficient days are provided for harvesting, planting and plowing. Our presence in the field facilitates constant monitoring and immediate reaction on the part of our legal team, particularly when violence erupts. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]14)
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]We put a great deal of effort into
[normal] document
[normal]ing
[normal] and report
[normal]ing
[normal] the incidents of vandalism, violence and inaction by local military and police units, sharing this information with the DCO, police national command, army legal advisors office, regional commanders, the media, concerned foreign d
[normal]elegations and international organizations in an effort to advocate for change. We demand increased efforts on the part of the responsible Israeli authorities to enforce the right to security of person and property for all civilians in the areas of continu
[normal]ing Israeli military rule until there is a political solution to the situation, not only during the Palestinian olive harvest season but throughout the year
[normal]. 
[normal]Our media team work
[normal]s
[normal] to draw media attention to the violations taking place
[normal] and publish
[normal]es
[normal] stories 
[normal]of attacks on farmers. 
