[normal]Project 
[normal]evaluation
[normal] methods are designed into all of RHR’s projects. 
[normal]Department heads are tasked with evaluating their projects on an ongoing basis, getting feedback from staff, project participants and the target populations 
[normal]themselves. W
[normal]hen necessary we adjust programs midstream in order to sharpen the focus of our work, ultimately making the program more effective. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]16)
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]Our senior managerial staff, legal staff, field team and media team work hand in hand and support each other's work through transfer of information, joint cooperation and monitoring and documenting the impact of our work. 
[normal]RHR is expanding its capacity in t
[normal]he traditional media as well as in online new-media. 
[normal]O
[normal]ur public education efforts through traditional media and new media 
[normal]are
[normal] essential to change perspectives and many basic assumptions within Israeli society. 
[normal]Our media team 
[normal]a
[normal]ssess
[normal]es
[normal] the degree of success 
[normal]in quantity and effectiveness of media coverage of the legal work, agricultural work and
[normal] Jahalin
[normal] project in general and framing of the issue among the Israeli public and political leaders specifically as one of Jewish and democratic legal values.
