[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]17)
[normal]&#xa0; 
[normal]Due to 
[normal]the volatile nature of the context of RHR’s work, there are inherent challenges in ensuring successes are permanent and sustainable. Even where legal precedents are set, often counter legal advocacy overturns successful outcomes
[normal] and the
[normal] implementation of rulings 
[normal]needs to be monitored
[normal]. 
[normal]Our work on land issues addresses the most intractable and challenging issue at the source of the Israeli-Palestinian conflict. Thereby, new challenges will always have to be addressed as they appear. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]While dealing with issues of land takeovers, demolitions and expulsions RHR’s focus is changing the status quo – challenging the
[normal] root causes of human rights violations
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]T
[normal]here is a risk that some forms of legal assistance only combat the symptoms of violat
[normal]ions rather than their causes. 
[normal]In order to address this challenge, 
[normal]RHR’s legal department 
[normal]attempts to 
[normal]challenge the underlying system
[normal] 
[normal]through strategic litigation
[normal],
[normal] focusing on precedent settin
[normal]g cases that if successful, could
[normal] impact the lives of landowners
[normal],
[normal] if not throughout the OPT, at least in Area C. 
